p>0
\sum^{\infty}_{n=1} (-1)^{n} \int^{\pi}_{0} (x+n\pi)^{-p}\sin{(x)} dx
x\in[0,\pi]
a_{n} > 0
a_{n}
a_{n} = \int^{\pi}_{0} (x+n\pi)^{-p}\sin{(x)} dx
a_n
x + (n+1) \pi > x + n \pi
\int_0^\pi (x + (n+1)\pi)^{-p} \sin(x) \, dx \le \int_0^\pi (x + n \pi)^{-p} \sin(x) \, dx.
n\in\Bbb N
\frac{\sin x}{(x+n\pi)^p}<\frac{\sin x}{[x+(n+1)\pi]^p}
